property.description:
Defines a single property for a model.Example:```
    "age" : {
      "type": "number"
    }
```

propertyIndex.description:
Add an index to a property
@example
```
{
  "property_foo": { "type": "String", "index": true },
  "email": { "type": "String", "index": {"unique": true} },
}
```

acls.description:
The value of the `acls` key is an array of objects that describes the access controls for the model.

```
"acls": [
    {
      "permission": "ALLOW",
      "principalType": "ROLE",
      "principalId": "$everyone",
      "property": "myMethod"
    }, 
    ...
]
```
@see https://docs.strongloop.com/display/public/APIC/Model+definition+JSON+file#ModeldefinitionJSONfile-ACLs

scopes.description:
Scopes enable you to specify commonly-used queries that you can reference as method calls on a model.
The scopes key defines one or more scopes (named queries) for models. A scope maps a name to a predefined filter object to be used by the model's `find()` method

@example
```
"scopes": {
    "vips": {"where": {"vip": true}}, 
    "top5": {"limit": 5, "order": "age"}
}
```

@see https://docs.strongloop.com/display/public/APIC/Model+definition+JSON+file#ModeldefinitionJSONfile-Scopes
